<Base title="About" description="The dubious history of Perni Cious Remedies.">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 prose-gothic">
    <p class="eyebrow text-center">A Brief History</p>
    <h1 class="text-center mt-2">The Matter of Our Provenance</h1>
    <hr class="rule" />

    <p class="text-lg">
      Perni Cious Remedies was founded, allegedly, in a damp corner of the late 19th century
      by a man whose credentials could not be confirmed, whose recipes could not be verified,
      and whose business practices would not survive a modern audit.
    </p>

    <p>
      Every bottle in our collection is printed, sealed, and shipped in the present day.
      Every label is a fiction. Every claim is intentionally unfounded. Every tonic inside
      each bottle is <em>nothing</em> — these are decorative vessels, not beverages, not
      medicines, not even particularly decent ideas.
    </p>

    <p>
      We make them because we believe the world deserves more earnest absurdity on its shelves.
      Because a gothic home bar is improved by a bottle labelled <em>Unsolicited Opinions
      Suppressant</em>. Because a curio cabinet benefits from a <em>Widow's Tonic</em>
      that nobody drank and nobody will.
    </p>

    <p>
      Each bottle is UV-printed by hand in a small studio using archival-quality ink.
      We make them in short runs, we photograph them dramatically, and we send them
      to you wrapped in kraft paper and a warning.
    </p>

    <p class="eyebrow text-center mt-12">— The Proprietor</p>
  </article>
</Base>
